            "whatYouBring": "-U.A.E National that holds an accredited Bachelor’s degree from a recognized institution.\r-Demonstrated experience in assessing project risks and understanding the associated contingencies.\r-You are creative, self-motivated, and work well in dynamic, yet changing environment.",
            "tasks": "As an Assistant Project Manager, you will join the rail practice that covers all aspects of project life cycle from concept to construction. Day-to-day you will be immersed with a team that is diverse and committed to delivering services and solutions to our rail clients. You will be in a position to assist with rail assignments, and engaging with engineers, architects, environmental consultants, client and wider stakeholders to ensure project delivery and commercial success.  In this role you will assist Rail Project Managers with project planning, implementation, and completion of assigned projects.\rYou will be empowered to assist with long-range and short-term rail planning and design projects. You will be responsible for conducting studies, planning research alongside preparing reports and recommendations. You will have autonomy over developing projects plan and schedules using MS Project or Primavera setting milestones and timelines with the expected deliverables.\r",
            "benefits": "By joining Jacobs you will unlock a world of professional development and networking opportunities. With our global presence across 40+ countries, you'll have the opportunity to connect and work with some of the world’s most talented and influential professionals, expanding your reach and opening doors to new horizons.\rJob stability is paramount, and we understand your need for a secure future, by joining Jacobs you will benefit from our strong global pipeline of work providing you with a solid foundation to take your career to new heights.\r",
            "trainingDevelopment": null,
            "interviewProcess": null,
            "visaSponsorchip": null,
            "securityClearance": "-Demonstrated experience in assessing project risks and understanding contingencies",
            "Overview": "- Jacobs is a leading American international firm that offers a broad spectrum of professional services, including engineering, technical, professional, and construction services, as well as scientific and specialty consulting. Established in 1947 by Joseph J. Jacobs, the company is headquartered in Dallas, Texas, and generates over $14 billion in annual revenue.\n- The company serves a diverse range of clients across commercial, industrial, and governmental sectors, focusing on areas such as advanced manufacturing, energy, environment, health, life sciences, infrastructure, national security, and space. Jacobs is a Fortune 500 company with operations in over 40 countries and is consistently ranked highly in industry lists like *Engineering News-Record*'s Top 500 Design Firms.\n- Jacobs provides a comprehensive suite of services, including engineering and construction, consulting and technical services, and scientific and specialty consulting. These services encompass design-build services, construction management, infrastructure development, cybersecurity, data analytics, enterprise IT, and software development.\n- The company's approach is centered around creating sustainable and innovative solutions to address global challenges like climate change and urbanization. Committed to achieving net-zero greenhouse gas emissions by 2040, Jacobs is recognized for its sustainability initiatives.\n- Strategically, Jacobs has expanded its capabilities and market reach through acquisitions and partnerships. Notable acquisitions include CH2M Hill in 2017 and Wood Nuclear in 2020, which have bolstered its expertise in infrastructure, government services, and nuclear services.",
            "cultureValues": "- **We do things right.** We always act with integrity – taking responsibility for our work, caring for our people and staying focused on safety and sustainability. We make investments in our clients, people and communities, so we can grow together.\n\n- **We challenge the accepted.** We know that to create a better future, we must ask difficult questions. We always stay curious and are not afraid to try new things.\n\n- **We aim higher.** We do not settle – always looking beyond to raise the bar and deliver with excellence. We are committed to our clients by bringing innovative solutions that lead to profitable growth and shared success.\n\n- **We live inclusion.** We put people at the heart of our business. We embrace different perspectives, collaborating to make a positive impact. Through an unparalleled focus on inclusion with a diverse team of visionaries, thinkers and doers, we build trust – in each other and across our company.",
            "environmentSustainability": "- Jacobs' environment and sustainability strategy is centered around creating a positive impact through innovative solutions and sustainable practices.\n- The company has implemented the PlanBeyond℠ 2.0 strategy, which aligns with the United Nations Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) and integrates sustainability across its operations and client solutions.\n- A key component of this strategy is the Climate Action Plan, which aims to make every project a climate response opportunity and achieve net-zero greenhouse gas emissions across the value chain by 2040.\n- Jacobs has already made significant progress, including reducing carbon emissions by 45% since 2019 and procuring 100% low-carbon electricity for its operations.\n- Additionally, Jacobs focuses on regenerative and nature-based solutions to restore and protect natural ecosystems, contributing to sustainable economic and social development.\n- The company measures its success through various metrics, such as its inclusion in the Dow Jones Sustainability World Index and the achievement of carbon neutrality.",
            "inclusionDiversity": "- Jacobs' inclusion and diversity strategy is aimed at fostering an environment where diverse employees feel welcomed, valued, and empowered to thrive.\n- The company has implemented several initiatives to achieve this goal, including the TogetherBeyond℠ strategy, which promotes inclusive behaviors and enhances diversity across all organizational levels.\n- A notable aspect of their strategy is the global Action Plan for Advancing Justice and Equality, which builds on existing efforts to address systemic inequalities and promote fairness.\n- Jacobs has set ambitious goals, such as achieving a 40-40-20 gender-balanced workforce, comprising 40% women, 40% men, and 20% flexible.\n- The company measures success through various metrics, including the diversity composition of its Executive Leadership Team, which is 63% diverse and 40% female.",
