            "whatYouBring": "-Ability to work to tight deadlines and prioritization of work to achieve them.\r-Sound knowledge of International codes and standards related to telecommunication field.\r-Design experience in various long haul transmission systems encompassing SDH/PDH nodes, MPLS TP node, Gigabit Ethernet switches etc.\r-Interface requirements with various Control systems, Electrical Systems etc.",
            "tasks": "-Perform Telecom engineering design duties associated Green field and brown field off shore and on shore oil and gas processing facilities and downstream facilities such as refinery, petrochemicals, etc.\r-Duties will include data gathering and site survey of existing telecom systems.\r-Preparation of Front end engineering deliverables including design basis, specifications datasheets, sizing calculations, studies and reports.\r-Preparation of FEED and detail design deliverables such as Block Diagrams, Location Layouts, Cable Routing Layouts, Interconnection drawings etc. in collaboration with designers.\r-Carry out bid evaluation/ vendor document review and approval.\r-Co-ordination and network design / interface with required Process Control & Safety systems\r-Quality Assurance – Responsible for working within the provisions and guidelines of the Quality Assurance system relevant to the Oil & Gas Business Unit\r-Safety – Responsible for personal safety safe working practices for the Oil & Gas Business Unit. Understand and follow OH&S procedures.\r-Exposure to man-hour estimate and preparation of proposals.\r-Work is performed in accordance with broad technical guidelines and with minimal supervision.\r-Willing to learn and work on other areas such as instrumentation and control systems if project demands or opportunity is given within organization.\r-Execution of Telecommunications projects; both standalone and integrated.\r-Design of systems such as Telephone System, LAN System, TETRA System, Microwave Radio, VHF Marine Radio, VSAT, PAGA, ACS, CCTV, Intruder detection system, Structured Cabling System, FO Cabling, Telephone cabling etc. to suit client requirements\r-Preparation of Telecom system specifications and equipment datasheets.\r-Preparation of Technical Bid evaluation and recommendations.\r-FO link budget calculations, Bandwidth requirements, Radio coverage study, Speaker coverage calculations etc. using standard software’s available in telecom industry. \r-QA - Responsible for working with the provisions and guidelines of company QA procedures",
            "benefits": null,
            "trainingDevelopment": null,
            "interviewProcess": null,
            "visaSponsorchip": null,
            "securityClearance": "-Responsible for working within the provisions and guidelines of the Quality Assurance (QA) system relevant to the Oil & Gas Business Unit",
            "Overview": "- Worley is a global professional services company headquartered in Australia, specializing in the energy, chemicals, and resources sectors.\n- With a history spanning over 50 years, Worley has evolved from a small engineering consultancy into a leading solutions provider.\n- The company is renowned for its expertise in project delivery, offering comprehensive services that cover the entire lifecycle of a project—from the initial engineering stages to installation, commissioning, and eventual decommissioning and remediation.\n- Worley is committed to facilitating the transition to more sustainable energy systems by bridging the gap between traditional fossil fuels and renewable energy sources.\n- This involves a strategic balance between conventional and sustainable practices, ensuring that they meet the current demands of society while paving the way for a more sustainable future.\n- Worley's approach is data-centric, leveraging innovative technologies to enhance project execution and asset management across various scales, from small facilities to multi-billion-dollar projects worldwide.",
            "cultureValues": "- **We value life:** We believe in the safety, health and wellbeing of our people, communities and the environment. Without it, nothing else matters.\n\n- **We rise to the challenge:** We love a challenge. We go the extra mile delivering new and better solutions to complex problems.\n\n- **We are stronger together:** We thrive in real relationships and partnerships. We nurture networks and collaboration. We recognize our differences make us stronger.\n\n- **We unlock brilliance:** We are passionate about innovating and learning. We value, share and grow our expertise.",
            "environmentSustainability": "- Worley's environment and sustainability strategy is centered on facilitating the global transition to a lower-carbon economy while maintaining its role in traditional energy sectors.\n- The company is committed to delivering sustainable change by integrating sustainability into its core operations and project delivery.\n- Worley has set a target to achieve net zero emissions for Scope 1 and Scope 2 by 2030, and for Scope 3 by 2050. Scope 1 and 2 emissions primarily involve direct emissions from owned or controlled sources and indirect emissions from the generation of purchased energy, respectively.\n- Worley employs a data-driven approach, utilizing tools like IBM Envizi to capture and analyze corporate environmental metrics and activity data, which helps in tracking progress and measuring success in sustainability efforts.\n- One of Worley's key initiatives is bridging the gap between conventional and renewable energy sources, aiming to support the shift towards more sustainable energy systems. This includes projects in renewable energy, sustainable chemicals, and materials required for technologies like batteries.",
            "inclusionDiversity": "- Worley's inclusion and diversity strategy is focused on creating a workplace that values and leverages the diversity of its people to enhance business results and foster a more inclusive environment.\n- The company has set specific goals to increase diversity within its workforce, including a target to have 30% of its workforce comprised of women by 2025.\n- Currently, women make up 20.8% of the entire workforce and 33% of the board, with 48% of new graduates being women, indicating progress towards these goals.\n- Worley also emphasizes gender equity, particularly in supporting women in STEM careers, through initiatives led by the Worley Foundation.\n- Success in these efforts is measured by tracking workforce composition and progress towards set targets, as well as the implementation of policies that prevent discrimination based on race, ethnicity, and other grounds.",
