            "whatYouBring": "  - Bachelor’s degree in Civil Engineering, Construction Management, or a related field.\r  - Minimum of 15 years of experience in road construction, with a focus on grading operations.\r  - Proficiency in engineering design software (e.g., AutoCAD, Civil 3D).\r  - Strong understanding of soil mechanics, drainage systems, and road construction techniques.\r  - Excellent problem-solving and analytical skills.\r  - Strong communication and interpersonal skills.\r  - Ability to work collaboratively in a team environment.\r- Valid driver’s license in UAE\r- Professional Engineer (PE) license preferred.\r- Willingness to travel to various project sites as needed.\r",
            "tasks": "The person is responsible for planning, designing, and overseeing the construction and maintenance of road grading projects. This role involves ensuring that road surfaces are correctly graded to promote efficient drainage and to prepare the foundation for subsequent layers of road construction. The engineer will work closely with construction teams, surveyors, and project managers to deliver high-quality road infrastructure.\r  - Develop detailed grading plans and specifications based on engineering principles and project requirements.\r  - Conduct site assessments and surveys to gather data for designing road grades and alignments.\r  - Utilize software tools (e.g., AutoCAD, Civil 3D) for creating grading plans and profiles.\r  - Supervise and monitor grading operations to ensure compliance with design specifications and safety standards.\r  - Coordinate with construction teams, surveyors, and other stakeholders to address any on-site issues and ensure timely project completion.\r  - Perform quality control inspections and assessments to verify that grading work meets engineering standards and project requirements.\r  - Provide technical guidance and support to construction teams regarding grading techniques and best practices.\r  - Identify and resolve engineering problems related to grading, drainage, and soil stabilization.\r  - Recommend modifications to grading plans as necessary to accommodate site conditions and project changes.\r  - Ensure all grading activities comply with local, state, and federal regulations and industry standards.\r  - Maintain accurate project documentation, including grading plans, inspection reports, and as-built drawings.\r  - Prepare progress reports and communicate project status to stakeholders.\rAtkinsRealis is committed to eliminating discrimination and encouraging diversity amongst our workforce. We aim to provide quality and fairness for all job applicants and employees and not to discriminate on grounds of gender, marital status, age, race, ethnic origin, religious conviction or disablement. We oppose all forms of unlawful treatment and discrimination.\rHaving clear and concise procedures and guidelines for both line managers and employees to ensure policies are fully understood and implemented;\rComplying with the relevant employment legislation and codes of practice;\rEnsuring that all existing employees, potential employees, colleagues and customers are treated equally and with respect;\rEnsuring that the workplace is an environment free from discrimination, harassment, victimisation and bullying regardless of an individual’s gender, marital status, age, race, ethnic origin, religious conviction or disablement;\rMaking all decisions relating to recruitment, selection or promotion according to the employees’ ability.\r",
            "benefits": "-A competitive salary\r-Transportation allowance\r-Medical and life insurance cover\r-22 calendar days annual leave\r-Company gratuity scheme\r-Discretionary bonus scheme\r-Annual flight allowance to point of origin",
            "trainingDevelopment": null,
