            "whatYouBring": "-Bachelor's degree in accounting, finance, BA\r-Excellent communication skills, written, oral, and presentation\r-Ability to work as part of a team\r-Strong use of Microsoft Word, Excel and PowerPoint",
            "tasks": "-Ability to prioritize key tasks and solve problems for the team\r-Maximise commercial performance while managing business/project risk (pre and post-contract)\r-Commercialisation of a sub-Business Groups service offerings to support business growth and strategy\r-Ensure compliance with relevant commercial/contracting policies\r-Resolution of disputes/claims and cash collection issues\r-Embedding effective commercial governance and assurance across the sub-Business Group / Project / Portfolio of Projects\r-Supporting the tender governance process for the sub-Business Group\r-Promote and demonstrate safety leadership behaviors\r-Always act ethically and with the utmost integrity\r-Champion and promote the application of the Financial Management Framework guidelines\r-Champion and follow the relevant DOA and commercial / contracting policies",
