            "securityClearance": "-Always act ethically and with utmost integrity, champion and promote the application of Financial Management Framework guidelines, follow relevant DOA and commercial/contracting policies",
            "Overview": "- Wood Plc, headquartered in Aberdeen, Scotland, is a global leader in consulting and engineering, primarily serving the energy and materials markets.\n- Established in 1982, the company provides a wide array of services including project and construction management, operations and maintenance, and engineering design across various sectors such as oil and gas, chemicals, renewable energy, and infrastructure.\n- Wood has offices in Australia, Canada, England, UAE, the US, and other countries.\n- Increasingly focused on sustainable energy and decarbonization technologies such as carbon capture, hydrogen technology, and renewable energy sources like solar, wind, wave, tidal, and biofuels.\n- Sustainable solutions now represent over 40% of their bidding pipeline, indicating a significant shift towards green initiatives.\n- The company reported revenues of approximately $5.9 billion, reflecting an 8% increase from the previous year’s $5.5 billion. The company’s adjusted EBITDA grew by 9%, reaching $423 million.\n- Wood offers an integrated service model including advisory on feasibility, concept design, strategy planning, design services from FEED to detailed design, delivery services like PMC and EPCm, operational support including maintenance and asset optimization, and repurposing services for life extension and decommissioning.",
            "cultureValues": "- **Wood PLC** is committed to fostering a culture that emphasizes collaboration, innovation, and excellence. The company's culture is built around creating an environment where employees enjoy coming to work and clients are eager to engage with them. This is achieved through a focus on their core values and behaviors, which include commitment, courage, and agility in delivering solutions. Wood PLC's leadership plays a crucial role in monitoring and nurturing this culture, ensuring that it is effectively implemented across the organization through regular engagement with the workforce.\n- The company's values are designed to support its strategic goals, which are structured around three main pillars: **Inspired Culture, Performance Excellence, and Profitable Growth.** These pillars guide the company's operations and decision-making processes, aligning with the needs of their employees, clients, and shareholders. Wood PLC aims to leverage the expertise and dedication of its global team to drive sustainable solutions and make a meaningful impact on the world.",
            "environmentSustainability": "- **Wood PLC's** environmental and sustainability strategy is focused on addressing climate change and supporting their clients in achieving their sustainability goals. The company has set ambitious targets to reduce its carbon footprint and enhance its sustainability practices. Wood aims to achieve net-zero carbon emissions by 2050, aligning its efforts with global standards such as the Paris Agreement. The company is committed to reducing its Scope 1 and Scope 2 emissions, which include direct fuel consumption and indirect emissions from purchased electricity, respectively.\n- To achieve these goals, Wood is implementing a range of initiatives, including transitioning to renewable energy sources and enhancing energy efficiency across its operations. The company is also focused on reducing the use of single-use plastics and promoting sustainable practices within its supply chain. Additionally, Wood is actively involved in projects related to renewable energy, hydrogen, carbon capture and storage, and other sustainable solutions, which represent a significant portion of its revenue.\n- In terms of results, Wood has made substantial progress in its sustainability efforts. The company has increased its focus on sustainable solutions, with approximately 21% of its group revenue coming from these activities. Furthermore, around 40% of its sales pipeline is now comprised of sustainable solutions, reflecting Wood's commitment to driving the energy transition and supporting a more sustainable future. Through these efforts, Wood PLC is positioning itself as a leader in sustainable practices within the engineering and construction industry.\n- Achieved a 20% reduction in Scope 1 and 2 emissions in 2022, cumulatively reducing these emissions by 65% from the 2019 baseline.\n- 55% of Wood’s purchased electricity now comes from certified renewable energy sources.\n- Continues active participation in oil and gas sectors while implementing carbon capture and storage projects.\n- Have worked on more than half of the world’s carbon capture and storage projects.\n- Aiming for a Top Quartile position in ESG investment ratings among industry peers by 2025.\n- Member of the United Nations Global Compact, committing to uphold principles in human rights, labor, environment, and anti-corruption.\n- Holds an AA rating in the MSCI ESG Ratings and Silver in the 2023 Ecovadis Sustainability Rating.\n- Targets to have 100% of suppliers incorporate Building Responsibly Principles into their supply chains by 2030, with all labor suppliers expected to sign up and comply by 2025.",
            "inclusionDiversity": "- In 2022, **Wood PLC** achieved 32% female representation with a focused effort in 2023 on developing female P&L leaders and increasing female intake into Early Careers roles, where 48% of the intake was female.\n- Between 2022 and 2023, the mean Gender Pay Gap (GPG) reduced from 26.0% to 23.3%, and the mean bonus gap decreased from 44.2% to 13.2%. The median bonus gap improved to -0.7%.\n- Committed to increasing female leaders in senior leadership and technical positions, aiming for 40% female representation in leadership by 2030.\n- Plans include refreshing and expanding employee networks, empowering leadership teams with action plans for sustainable, inclusive change, maintaining focus on balanced early career stage intake, and ongoing tracking of diversity statistics.\n- Ensures fair pay practices, confirming that pay disparities are due to the gender distribution across roles, not equal pay issues.\n- Supports DEI through leadership champions and allies, active employee networks like the Wood Race and Ethnicity Network (WREN) and the Pride network.\n- DEI progress is measured quarterly, with oversight provided by the Board through the Nomination Committee.",
